OL,3,CWater first formed billions of years
OL,4,Cearlier than previously thought ` study
OL,6,FWater has been present in the universe
OL,7,Fsince 100-200 million years after the
OL,8,FBig Bang, scientists have discovered.
OL,10,FThe study, published in the journal
OL,11,FNature Astronomy, suggests that the
OL,12,Fdiscovery means that habitable planets
OL,13,Fcould have started forming billions of
OL,14,Fyears earlier than previously thought
OL,15,Fand before the first galaxies had even
OL,16,Fformed.
