OL,3,CWater first formed billions of years
OL,4,Cearlier than previously thought ` study
OL,6,FDr Daniel Whalen, from the University
OL,7,Fof Portsmouth's Institute of Cosmology
OL,8,Fand Gravitation, who led the study,
OL,9,Fsaid that it was the first time that
OL,10,Fwater had been modelled in the
OL,11,Fprimordial universe.
OL,13,FAccording to the simulations used for
OL,14,Fthe research, water molecules began
OL,15,Fforming shortly after the first
OL,16,Fsupernova explosions, known as
OL,17,FPopulation III (Pop III) supernovae.
OL,19,FThese were essential for the creation
OL,20,Fof heavy elements such as oxygen which
OL,21,Fare required for water to exist.
