OL,3,CWater first formed billions of years
OL,4,Cearlier than previously thought ` study
OL,6,FDr Whalen said: "Before the first
OL,7,Fstars exploded, there was no water in
OL,8,Fthe universe because there was no
OL,9,Foxygen. Only very simple nuclei
OL,10,Fsurvived the Big Bang ` hydrogen,
OL,11,Fhelium, lithium and trace amounts of
OL,12,Fbarium and boron.
OL,14,F"Oxygen, forged in the hearts of these
OL,15,Fsupernovae, combined with hydrogen to
OL,16,Fform water, paving the way for the
OL,17,Fcreation of the essential elements
OL,18,Fneeded for life."
