OL,3,CWater first formed billions of years
OL,4,Cearlier than previously thought ` study
OL,6,FDr Whalen explained that the team,
OL,7,Fwhich included scientists from the
OL,8,FUnited Arab Emirates University,
OL,9,Fexamined two types of supernovae.
OL,11,FThese were core-collapse supernovae,
OL,12,Fwhich produce a modest amount of heavy
OL,13,Felements, and the "more energetic" Pop
OL,14,FIII supernovae, which eject tens of
OL,15,Fsolar masses of metals into space.
OL,17,FThe study found that both types of
OL,18,Fsupernovae formed dense clumps of gas
OL,19,Fenriched with water.
