OL,3,CWater first formed billions of years
OL,4,Cearlier than previously thought ` study
OL,6,FDr Whalen said that although the
OL,7,Famounts of water produced was "modest"
OL,8,Fit was highly concentrated in cloud
OL,9,Fcores ` dense regions of gas ` which
OL,10,Fwere believed to be the birthplaces of
OL,11,Fstars and planets.
OL,13,FHe added: "The key finding is that
OL,14,Fprimordial supernovae formed water in
OL,15,Fthe universe that predated the first
OL,16,Fgalaxies. So water was already a key
OL,17,Fconstituent of the first galaxies.
