OL,6,F"This implies the conditions necessary
OL,7,Ffor the formation of life were in
OL,8,Fplace way earlier than we ever
OL,9,Fimagined ` it's a significant step
OL,10,Fforward in our understanding of the
OL,11,Fearly universe.
OL,13,F"Although the total water masses were
OL,14,Fmodest, they were highly concentrated
OL,15,Fin the only structures capable of
OL,16,Fforming stars and planets. And that
OL,17,Fsuggests that planetary discs rich in
OL,18,Fwater could form at cosmic dawn,
OL,19,Fbefore even the first galaxies."
